mibsS7ProfileTable.name: mibsS7ProfileTable
mibsS7ProfileTable.description: A list of mibsS7Profile profile entries.

mibsS7ProfileEntry.name: mibsS7ProfileEntry
mibsS7ProfileEntry.description: A mibsS7Profile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsS7Profile profile.

sS7Profile_Enabled.name: sS7Profile_Enabled
sS7Profile_Enabled.description: When set to 'no', interface to the SS7 gateway is disabled.

sS7Profile_ControlProtocol.name: sS7Profile_ControlProtocol
sS7Profile_ControlProtocol.description: Control protocol between the access server and the signaling gateway.

sS7Profile_PrimaryIpAddress.name: sS7Profile_PrimaryIpAddress
sS7Profile_PrimaryIpAddress.description: IP address of the primary SS7 gateway.

sS7Profile_PrimaryTcpPort.name: sS7Profile_PrimaryTcpPort
sS7Profile_PrimaryTcpPort.description: TCP port on primary SS7 gateway.

sS7Profile_SecondaryIpAddress.name: sS7Profile_SecondaryIpAddress
sS7Profile_SecondaryIpAddress.description: IP address of the secondary SS7 gateway.

sS7Profile_SecondaryTcpPort.name: sS7Profile_SecondaryTcpPort
sS7Profile_SecondaryTcpPort.description: TCP port on the secondary SS7 gateway.

sS7Profile_BayId.name: sS7Profile_BayId
sS7Profile_BayId.description: Bay ID defines the bay this device belongs to. Used for registration purposes only. The content of this field is reported to the gateway during the device registration process.

sS7Profile_SystemType.name: sS7Profile_SystemType
sS7Profile_SystemType.description: Model ID and/or type of equipment. Used for device registration only. Must be listed in the database on the Gateway.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Type.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Type
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Type.description: The type of transport layer that is to be used

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_DeviceId.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_DeviceId
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_DeviceId.description: A code that uniquely identifies this device to the Gateway. If multiple remote access servers are configured to use the same signaling gateway, every one of those servers must be assigned an identifier that is unique within the group.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T1Duration.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T1Duration
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T1Duration.description: Value of the ACK delay timer in milliseconds. This timer specifies the maximum delay for an acknowledgement when an I-frame is received. Default value is 1000 (1 second). The value must be less than T2 on the peer.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T2Duration.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T2Duration
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T2Duration.description: Value of the transmission timeout timer in milliseconds. This timer specifies how long this endpoint should wait for an acknowledgement. Default value is 3000 (3 seconds). The value must be greater than T1 on the peer.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T3Duration.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T3Duration
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_T3Duration.description: Value of the persistent error timer in milliseconds. This timer specifies the maximum duration of attempts to re-establish a link before the transport layer flushes the data queues and sends an error indication up. Default value is 30000 (30 seconds).

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_WindowSize.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_WindowSize
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_WindowSize.description: Maximum number of sequentially numbered data packets that can be sent while pending acknowledgement at any given time. Default value is 7.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_AckThreshold.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_AckThreshold
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_AckThreshold.description: The threshold for triggering an acknowledgement while receiving data packets. As soon as the specified number of packets is received, an ACK is sent back regardless of the value of T1 timer. The value of this parameter may not be greater than the window size. Default value is 6.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_HeartBeat.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_HeartBeat
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_HeartBeat.description: When set to 'no', layer 2 heartbeat mechanism is not enabled.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Active.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Active
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Active.description: Activate type of service for this connection.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Preceden.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Precedence
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Preceden.description: Tag the precedence bits (priority bits) in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_TypeOfSe.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_TypeOfService
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_TypeOfSe.description: Tag the type of service field in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_ApplyTo.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_ApplyTo
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_ApplyTo.description: Define how the type-of-service applies to data flow for this connection.

sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Dscp.name: sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Dscp
sS7Profile_TransportOptions_Tos_Dscp.description: DSCP tag to be used in marking of the packets (if marking-type = dscp).

sS7Profile_UseSystemIpAddressAsSource.name: sS7Profile_UseSystemIpAddressAsSource
sS7Profile_UseSystemIpAddressAsSource.description: When set to 'yes', use configured System IP Address as source ip address. When set to 'no', use IP Address of outgoing interface as source ip address.

sS7Profile_IpdcSourceAdddress.name: sS7Profile_IpdcSourceAdddress
sS7Profile_IpdcSourceAdddress.description: IP address to be used on the private network

sS7Profile_Vrouter.name: sS7Profile_Vrouter
sS7Profile_Vrouter.description: Specifies the virtual router to be used.

sS7Profile_CongestionControl_CongestionC.name: sS7Profile_CongestionControl_CongestionControlType
sS7Profile_CongestionControl_CongestionC.description: Type of the congestion control algorithm to use.

sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Level.name: sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Level
sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Level.description: The level at which 'congestion level 1' indication will be issued. The value is interpreted according to the configured congestion control 'type'.

sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Action.name: sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Action
sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl1Action.description: Action taken when congestion level 1 (defined by the value of cl1-level) is reached.

sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Level.name: sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Level
sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Level.description: The level at which 'congestion level 2' indication will be issued. The value is interpreted according to the configured congestion control 'type'.

sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Action.name: sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Action
sS7Profile_CongestionControl_Cl2Action.description: Action taken when congestion level 2 (defined by the value of cl2-level) is reached.

sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Enabled.name: sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Enabled
sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Enabled.description: When set to yes, TNT will generate signaling heartbeat to MGC based on the interval configured in signaling-heartbeat interval.

sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Interval.name: sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Interval
sS7Profile_SignalingHeartbeat_Interval.description: The time interval in seconds for layer 3 heartbeat messages.

sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Type.name: sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Type
sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Type.description: The type of resilience action required when line state changes.

sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Duration.name: sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Duration
sS7Profile_ResilienceOptions_Duration.description: The duration in milli seconds for which calls should be maintained when line state changes. Valid only if the type is configured as timed-release.

sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Enabled.name: sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Enabled
sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Enabled.description: When set to yes, we will synchronize the d-channel status with the IPDC signaling link state.

sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Duration.name: sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Duration
sS7Profile_PriTunnelingOptions_Duration.description: The duration in milliseconds after which bringing down D-channel of tunneled-pri-signaling lines will be initiated.

mibpRITunlStatProfileTable.name: mibpRITunlStatProfileTable
mibpRITunlStatProfileTable.description: A list of mibpRITunlStatProfile profile entries.

mibpRITunlStatProfileEntry.description: A mibpRITunlStatProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibpRITunlStatProfile profile.
